<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Frequent fires or other disturbances maintain this alliance because shrubs typically grow fast and flower quickly. Seeds will germinate without pretreatment (Mirov and Kraebel 1939, Schmidt 1980); however, seed germination may improve slightly with exposure to light and leachate from charred wood (Keeley 1987b). Sprouting occurs weakly from rooted stolons after light fires.</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Fire return interval</td>
			<td>Medium (20-50 years)
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
